						<summary>

						<p>This is an inscription assignable to Uttama-Chōḷa on account of the details of date given, which correspond to A.D. 982, June 9, Friday in the 13th year of the king. This registers a gift of land after purchase by <hi rend="bold">Vīranāraṇiyār a queen of Uttama-Chōḷa</hi> to the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭattu-Perumāḷ at Tirukkuḍamukkil, for providing for flower-garlands to the god.</p>						

						</summary>
